ng consumption with explicit typed events, trustworthy heartbeats, clear idle-vs-stuck semantics, replay-to-live handoff, and adaptive cadence behavior that stays aligned with the shared attention and transport contracts.","notes":"Operator checkpoint: feed-level adaptive cadence gap closed in internal/robot/attention_feed.go by suppressing ephemeral heartbeats when a recent durable event already proves liveness, while still emitting heartbeat after the quiet period with last_event_time/idle_ms metadata. Independent pane review says no material adaptive gap remains beyond SSE degraded/recovery behavior already handled in internal/serve/server.go. Full local Go verification is still pending because unrelated system-wide Rust compilation is starving the current worktree build/test path.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:02.724224253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:40:02.791512924Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:03.695584425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:07.706799550Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:02.724224253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:06.923200325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:06.156707440Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:05.389480671Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:04.526063040Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: durable escalation model for recurring operator pain","description":"Introduce a durable incident model for persistent and repeating problems such as crash loops, chronic rate limits, stale reservations, or long-lived stalls. This epic exists because transient alerts are not enough for operators to understand recurring pain or prioritize the work that keeps resurfacing.","design":"Incidents are meant to capture fingerprints, recurrence, severity, lifecycle state, and evidence links so that ntm can distinguish between one-off noise and real persistent operational trouble.\\n\\nThis is a controlled theft from vibe_cockpit's stronger escalation mindset, adapted to ntm's tmux-and-project workflow rather than to a fleet-monitoring worldview.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when repeated operational pain can be promoted, tracked, surfaced in snapshot/digest/attention, and closed explicitly instead of continually reappearing as disconnected warnings.","notes":"Incidents should help prioritize operator attention, not become a giant secondary ticketing system.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08.984551518Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T19:52:42.432239915Z","closed_at":"2026-03-26T19:52:42.431878689Z","close_reason":"All incident child beads bd-j9jo3.5.1 through bd-j9jo3.5.4 are closed; the epic is done and should stop appearing as open planning surface area.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08.984551518Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":317,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: keep the incident model narrow and operator-focused. If it starts feeling like generic ITSM, you've gone too far.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: define incident taxonomy and promotion rules","description":"Define which operator-visible problems stay as transient alerts and which ones should promote into durable incidents. This task exists so recurring or high-cost operational problems acquire lifecycle and memory instead of reappearing forever as disconnected warnings.","design":"The taxonomy should classify incident families such as crash loops, chronic quota pressure, repeated reservation conflicts, sustained stalls, unhealthy source outages, and broken coordination patterns. It should specify severity, promotion thresholds, deduplication/fingerprinting factors, resolution semantics, and how incidents relate to reason codes already used by attention and alerting.\\n\\nThe result should make incident behavior boring and predictable rather than heuristic folklore hidden in code.","acceptance_criteria":"Produce a self-contained incident taxonomy with promotion and resolution rules that downstream persistence and surface tasks can implement directly.\\n\\nThe taxonomy must explain what evidence accumulates an incident, what keeps it open, what resolves it, and how it differs from a momentary alert.","notes":"Incidents are worth adding only because they reduce operator cognitive load over time. If they become another noisy warning channel, this task failed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:11.826693809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:40:09.580941768Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:40:09.580386218Z","close_reason":"Completed docs/incident-taxonomy.md - 16 families, promotion rules, lifecycle","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alerts","incidents","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:53.877190027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:54.341697983Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:54.818470055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:11.826693809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":326,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"This bead captures a major architectural upgrade: ntm should remember persistent operator pain, not just report the latest symptoms.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:12Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","title":"robot-redesign/incidents: implement incident persistence, fingerprinting, and lifecycle","description":"Implement persistent incidents with stable fingerprints, evidence accumulation, severity, status, and lifecycle transitions. This task exists to turn the incident model into a durable operational memory instead of a conceptual label.","design":"The implementation should define how incidents are keyed, how evidence is appended or summarized, how recurrence is tracked, how resolution and reopening behave, and how incidents connect to source_health, attention events, and runtime projections.\\n\\nThis task should also decide how much historical detail is kept directly on the incident versus in linked events, with a bias toward clear operator semantics over maximal logging.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can create, update, resolve, reopen, and query durable incidents with stable fingerprints and lifecycle semantics grounded in the taxonomy bead.","notes":"A strong implementation here makes later attention and digest outputs feel much smarter without requiring any hand-wavy 'AI insight' layer.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:13.201293920Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T03:11:55.136314769Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T03:11:55.135806347Z","close_reason":"Completed: added durable incident fingerprint/family/category fields and migration, CreateOrUpdateIncident fingerprint lifecycle semantics, public GetIncidentByFingerprint queryability, reopen/new-after-window behavior with tests, and 7-day resolved-incident retention via RunGC.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["incidents","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:56.265139624Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_