-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: align JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse rendering with the shared section model","description":"Align all renderer variants with the same underlying section model so format differences do not create semantic drift. This task exists because alternate renderers are valuable, but only if they remain projections of the same facts.","design":"The work should identify which sections can be faithfully rendered in JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse forms, how section omission is signaled when formats intentionally compress information, how stable ordering survives format changes, and how truncation cues, omission reasons, and compact explanation handles remain explicit instead of being hidden inside formatter-specific behavior. Renderer-specific affordances should remain subordinate to shared semantics.\n\nThis task should reduce duplicated formatting logic that currently smuggles in different ideas of what the system state is.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when alternate renderers are visibly thin projections over the shared section model and when format changes no longer imply semantic changes.","notes":"Renderer diversity is fine; semantic divergence or hidden format-specific truncation is not.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"codex","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:19.443640478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:29:14.707698882Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["renderers","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:24.180659194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:35.626151138Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on