 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down","description":"Split the inspect-surface work so coordination-heavy drill-down does not stay entangled with session and agent drill-down. This task exists because work backlog, unread mail, reservation conflicts, handoffs, quota pressure, and incidents deserve a distinct operator-facing detail model from session/pane inspection.","design":"The work should define inspect views or modes for work items, coordination state, quota or health state, and incidents, including stable lookup keys, expected detail depth, how invalid or unsupported lookups are reported, and how these views are reached from snapshot and attention. It should also make clear where these detail surfaces stop, how they coordinate with the shared diagnostics flow for evidence, source-health causes, cursor or replay context, and incident reasoning, and why they do not become another dumping ground for raw subsystem output.\n\nThis task intentionally complements the session or agent inspect task instead of replacing it.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable semantics and focused operator value.","notes":"These inspect surfaces should explain coordination pain and remediation options, not merely restate the summary sections in a more verbose format.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:44.351219027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T19:19:32.440900692Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T19:19:32.440439428Z","close_reason":"Implemented projection-backed inspect-work, inspect-coordination, inspect-quota, and inspect-incident surfaces with stable lookup keys, CLI/schema/capabilities/registry wiring, and focused store-backed tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.664776955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:24.767812294Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:36.191711626Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:27.006775235Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:50.444589022Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:00.220431554Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:00.733775080Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:33.601302775Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:01.338317557Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:44.351219027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":330,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","author":"ubuntu","text":"Split out from the original all-in-one inspect bead to improve parallelism and reduce a planning bottleneck.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:45Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down across inspect surfaces","description":"Add structured diagnostics and explainability drill-down so operators can inspect why snapshot, status, digest, attention, and inspect views look the way they do. This task exists because recovery is faster and trust is higher when ntm can expose source degradation, cursor state, truncation, projection freshness, and incident or attention evidence directly from the shared model instead of from raw logs.","design":"The work should define focused inspect views or modes for source-health breakdown, projection-update status, replay-window and cursor diagnostics, bounded-output or truncation explanations, suppression or aggregation explanations, request-correlation or idempotency diagnostics, operator attention-state diagnostics such as why an item is snoozed, pinned, muted, resurfaced, or force-escalated, and incident or attention evidence summaries. It should decide which explanation handles are shown inline in summary surfaces and which details live only in deeper drill-down, while avoiding a new overview command or a generic debug dump. This bead should make explainability a disciplined part of the inspect family: targeted, machine-readable, and sourced from the shared projection model rather than ad hoc formatter text.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign can answer questions such as why is this section stale, why did this incident open, why is this cursor invalid or expired, why was this output truncated, why was this item suppressed or resurfaced, why is it pinned or snoozed, and which request or outcome this evidence belongs to through supported inspect surfaces with stable shared semantics.","notes":"This is about trust and debugging speed, not verbosity for its own sake. The diagnostics flow should shorten recovery loops for both machine and human operators.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:09:11.713088410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T19:42:29.065158277Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T19:42:29.064665073Z","close_reason":"Added structured diagnostics across inspect surfaces, including projection stale reasons, source-health breakdown, domain-specific explainability entries, and incident attention-state/cursor-window evidence backed by the shared projection store.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["diagnostics","inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:32.438181484Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:48.877332108Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:58.038207644Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:00.392438841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:18.249287076Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:30.183341957Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:29.487800896Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:51.068802912Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:32.789431718Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:30.808813660Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:34.444587091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:31.491786147Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:32.151803814Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:09:11.713088410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:33.475003652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:34.170842501Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":335,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: diagnostics must answer why no events are arriving, whether a stream is healthy-idle versus stalled, which filters are active, whether backpressure or boundedness suppressed delivery, and why a heartbeat or progress annotation did or did not appear.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:02Z"},{"id":344,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-diagnostics follow-up: inspect surfaces must explain whether a historical answer came from replay or cached reconstruction, why history is partial or unavailable, which retention or boundedness rule limited the view, and how an operator pivots from a live incident summary into a recent as-of explanation without raw event archaeology.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":354,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: diagnostics must explain not only why something is stale or prioritized, but also why content is visible, previewed, hashed, redacted, or withheld, including which disclosure rule or replay limit shaped the answer.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:23Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.7","title":"robot-redesign/registry: unify capabilities, schema docs, and command metadata","description":"Introduce a shared robot command and section registry that drives capabilities, help text, schema publication, and transport metadata. This epic exists because the current giant flag-dispatch style makes it too easy for implementation, docs, and capabilities to drift apart.","design":"The registry should become the single metadata source for: surface names, section ownership, schema IDs, argument docs, degraded-feature reporting, and output examples. Checked-in JSON schema artifacts should be treated as contract artifacts, not just reflective byproducts.\\n\\nThis keeps the API discoverable and reduces the maintenance cost of adding or changing surfaces.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when capabilities, help/schema output, and command metadata are generated from one shared source of truth and no longer depend on duplicated hand-maintained descriptions.","notes":"The goal is disciplined metadata, not a grand rewrite of Cobra for its own sake.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:11.451562933Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.684690167Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["registry","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:11.451562933Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":319,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the registry exists to prevent drift. If you find yourself editing three places to describe one surface, the registry work is incomplete.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:12Z"}]}
